  "theorem": "Nash Trap Stability (Individual Policy Gradient)",
  "statement": "In symmetric N-agent non-linear PGG with M/N < 1, the individual value function V_i(\u03bb_i; \u03bb_{-i}=\u03bb) has a unique interior stationary point \u03bb* where \u2202V_i/\u2202\u03bb_i = 0, satisfying \u2202\u00b2V_i/\u2202\u03bb_i\u00b2 < 0 (local maximum for unilateral deviation). This \u03bb* is the Nash Trap: no individual agent has incentive to deviate from \u03bb* in either direction.",
